MARK: released Libchipcard 3.9.5beta (2007/11/02)
===========================================================================


2007/11/02: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- LC_ClientPcsc_V_GetNextCard() no longer bails out if there is no
  reader, it just keeps on scanning for readers (in case a reader is
  plugged in after this function is called)


2007/11/01: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- added reader flag LC_READER_FLAGS_NO_MEMORY_SW.
  This is used with Kobil Advanced USB readers because these devices
  return neither SW1 nor SW2 for memory cards (such as KVK)
- driverifd: If the flag LC_READER_FLAGS_NO_MEMORY_SW is given and the
  currently inserted card is a memory card then SW1 and SW2 will be
  manufactured
- card commands: now empty card commands are allowed. Those commands
  provoke the new error code LC_Client_ResultDontExecute which means
  that this special command is not to be executed for the given reader
  or driver. This is needed for the Kobil Kaan Advanced (and possibly
  others) to ignore the command SELECT_MF.


===========================================================================
MARK: released Libchipcard 3.9.4beta (2007/10/27)
===========================================================================


2007/10/26: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- added reader entry for SCR3311 (with generic CCID driver)
- introduced local installation mode:
  This can be used on Linux (on Windows this mode is always used since we
  need relocatable files there).
  Normally on Linux this project is installed to a well defined prefix and
  in respect to the FHS.
  However, it might sometimes be interesting to be able to have a relocatable
  version of Libchipcard, too. That is Libchipcard looks for its data files 
  and plugins in folders below the location of the called executable (using
  binreloc).


===========================================================================
MARK: released Libchipcard 3.9.3beta (2007/10/24)
===========================================================================


2007/10/24: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- libchipcard client now also looks for driver description files in the
  client's data folder. On posix systems there is none, since there
  libchipcard's own ressource manager is used. On Windows however these files
  contain information which is needed to determine the driver and reader type
  from a given PC/SC reader name. This in turn is needed to adapt APDUs
  on Windows the same way we do it on POSIX systems.
- split driver description files folder of this package: One for posix
  (contains the same as before) and one for Windows, where we use other ways
  to determine the driver and reader type (see above)
  On posix systems these files are installed to the server's data folder,
  on Windows they are installed to the client's data folder.
- removed the need for a <var> section in driver description files. This was
  deprecated anyway and only used by the memcard class to see whether we have
  a buggy driver for Towitoko CDM (serial) which has a very low write 
  boundary. This is now expressed by the new reader flag 
  LC_READER_FLAGS_LOW_WRITE_BOUNDARY


2007/10/23: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- install README files to appdatadir and carddatadir to make it easier to
  find those folders when using the path manager (especially under WIN32)
- use GWEN_PathManager to retrieve client configuration and data files
- libchipcard now cross-compiles for WIN32 using mingw32 on Debian.
  The resulting binaries work on Windows XP :-)


2007/10/12: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- removed old crypt token stuff


2007/09/28: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- driver_ifd now tries to select the protocol if the reader's default
  protocol doesn't work (this allows reading KVK cards with the Kobil Kaan
  Advanced)


2007/09/18: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- some fixes for DDVCard CryptToken, adapted to changes in the CryptToken API


2007/09/13: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- fixed a typo (spotted by Marcel Naziri)


