------------------------------------------------
- added special path for PC/SC drivers under SuSE


2007/04/19: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- adapted driver for IFD handlers for 64 bit archs: unfortunately PC/SC
  defines DWORD as "unsigned long" on any architecture, even on 64 bit.
  As a result DWORD is 32 bits wide on 32 bit archs and 64 bits wide on
  64 bit archs. The drivers seem to be expecting this behaviour so we have to
  use the same albeit incorrect definitions here


2007/04/11: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- fixed reader description for O2Micro
- fixed compile bug in src/lib/sharedstuff


