2006/10/20: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- added reader flag "keepRunning", which is used for SCM SPR532, because this
  reader doesn't like to be stopped (it can't be restarted afterwards, and
  since the manufacturers driver isn't OpenSource I don't know how to fix it)
- src/lib/sharedstuff/msgengine.c: Don't AND the tag type with 0x1f, this
  would make some tags unavailable (especially some KVK tags)


2006/10/19: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- changed the driver description files regarding SCM SPR532: Now we only
  support the original driver with the original firmware, because the
  generic CCID driver is unable to perform secure pin verification with
  some cards


2006/10/13: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- make use of the latest additions to the Cyberjack driver
- we are now fully capable of distinguishing two or more Cyberjack
  readers which are connected in parallel


2006/10/10: Martin Preuss<martin@libchipcard.de>
------------------------------------------------
- fixed a showstopper: If a reader reports an error while it is still being
  started the daemon could crash
- added nonstandard locations for CCID driver
- pcmciascanner and usbttyscanner now add device path information if available
- simplified card command description for PERFORM_VERIFICATION with the
  generic CCID driver (it now works with Kobil Kaan Advanced USB and 
  Omnikey CardMan 3621)
- added some more readers to the list of devices I tested myself
- cardcommander3: added command "rapdu" which sends an APDU to a reader
- the command IsoPerformModification_Ascii now works with both Kobil Kaan
  Advanced USB and Omnikey Cardman 3621. This allows changing the pin of
  STARCOS cards again
- added chipcardd3 command "listreaders": This command lists all supported
  readers
- improved handling of STARCOS cards: Now check for EF_CARD_VERSION. If it
  exists it might tell us what kind of card is inserted


